# Bell state — the "hello world" of entanglement.
#
# H puts q0 into an equal superposition; CNOT then entangles q1 with it. The
# result is (|00> + |11>)/sqrt(2): measuring the two qubits always gives matching
# results (00 or 11, 50/50), never 01 or 10.
qubits 2

H q0
CNOT q0 q1

MEASURE q0
MEASURE q1
